Incident: Whoami Command Detected in Request Body

Indicators:
Alert Trigger Reason : Possible IDOR Attack Detected
Source IP: 134.209.118.137
Source port: 49211
Destination IP: 172.16.17.15
Destination Port: 443

Investigation:
Understanding why alert was triggered:
  consecutive requests to the same page

Traffic information:
SOURCE:
  After researching ip address using ARIN Whois/RDAP, The IP address is owned by DIGITALOCEAN, a cloud service provider.

DESTINATION:
  The destination is a webserver on the simulated SIEM.

PROTOCOL
  The protocol being used: HTTPS

Findings:
  An attacker using a cloud service provider domain to attempt an IDOR attack, they repeateadly tried to get different users info.

This user is not on the company network.

After looking through logs the attacker did multiple requests attempting to get other users info. This traffic is malicous.

Just to be sure, I analyzed the email logs to check if this was a scheduled test, it was not. Nothing like that was ever mentioned.

The traffic flow is Internet -> Company network.

After analysing the logs, the injection attempts all resulted in response code 200, these requests went through and sent back data.

Conclusion:
True positive alert.

Response:
Requests were successful, first contain the system, then escalate the alert.
